The paper deals with the computational complexity of recognizing a language, which is a central topic in computational complexity theory (cs.CC). The use of multiple tapes and heads is a common technique in automata theory and formal language theory (cs.FL). The paper also involves the analysis of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS), as well as information theory (cs.IT) and logic (cs.LO).
